<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Suspect1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Suspect,</orth> subst. suspicion: <cit><quote>her rash s. she doth extenuate,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1010" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1010</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the ornament of beauty is s., a crow that flies in heaven's sweetest air,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 70.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 70, 3</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.139" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.140" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 140</bibl> (O. Edd. <emph>suspence</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.139" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.1.142" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 1, 142</bibl> <cit><quote>(have you in s.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.89" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 89</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>( --s).</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.5.32" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 32</bibl></cit> (Ff <emph>--s</emph>). <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.519" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 519</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.519" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 519</bibl> With <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>if some s. of ill masked not thy show,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 70.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 70, 13</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>